What You can do...
‚ñ™Ô∏èCarry a reusable bag with you and take enough for your shopping.
‚ñ™Ô∏èCarry a reusable cup for your coffee.
‚ñ™Ô∏èTake your own water with you so you don't have to buy a plastic bottle.
‚ñ™Ô∏èGet rid of clingfilm - there are plenty of suitable alternatives.
‚ñ™Ô∏èDon't use plastic straws! Paper and metal ones are now available.
‚ñ™Ô∏è Swap to soap bars to banish plastics from your basin.
‚ñ™Ô∏èGo green with your cleaning - there are so many options out there but my favourites are @smolproducts for dishwasher tablets and @oceansaverdrops for all my cleaning products.
‚ñ™Ô∏èLook out for plastics in your beauty regime. @upcirclebeauty products come in recyclable packaging and makes your skin glow and I've recently ordered from @desirootsbeauty which also uses recyclable packaging for their cream and thinks about all the ingredients used in their products.
